<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861224-0009 </DOCNO><HL> Credit Rating</HL><DD> 12/24/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> JOYBOND MARKET NEWS (BON)FINANCIAL, INSURANCE, MUTUAL FUNDS, ACCOUNTING, LEASING (FIN) </IN><DATELINE> JOY MANUFACTURING CO.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Moody's Investors Service Inc. placed $8 million of long-term debt of the Pittsburgh maker of oil field and petroleum equipment and coal mining machinery under review for possible downgrade. Under review are Joy's single-A-3 senior debt rating and the company's Prime-2 rating for commercial paper. Moody's cited the company's announcement Monday that it would go private in a leveraged buyout valued at $620 million. Moody's said it is assessing the impact of the proposed transaction on the company's leverage, cash flow, debt protection measurements and financial flexibility. A Joy spokeswoman declined to comment. </TEXT></DOC>